name: The Pantry
description: Traditionele en huisgemaakte gerechten uit de Nederlandse keuken. Bij The Pantry proeft u hoe de Nederlandse keuken smaakt. Wij serveren verse, huisgemaakte gerechten gebaseerd op traditionele recepten. Kom oer-Hollands lunchen of dineren in onze huiskamersfeer of op ons terras. Proef onze Nederlandse wijn uit de Gelderse Achterhoek. Proost met een van onze lokale (speciaal) bieren. Geniet na van uw diner met een oer-Hollandse jenever of likeur. Bekijk hier onze menukaart.

The restaurant itself has a cozy and warm atmosphere, and the staffs were friendly enough in Amsterdam.

However, the space felt a bit chaotic due to the high number of diners in such a small area. The tables were placed very close together, making it easy to overhear conversations from neighboring tables, which detracted from the overall experience.

We had the pleasure of dining at The Pantry, and it was a truly wonderful experience. From the moment we walked in, we were greeted with warm smiles and a welcoming atmosphere. The decor is charming and cozy, making it the perfect place to relax and enjoy a meal.

The menu offers a fantastic variety of dishes, each more tempting than the last. We decided to try several Dutch specialties like Herring and Mini Pancakes, and they did not disappoint! The flavors were perfectly balanced, and the presentation was beautiful.

The staff were attentive and friendly, always ensuring that we had everything we needed. With my restricted diet, we had to make sure the food was suitable, and the waiters were very helpful in explaining the ingredients and making recommendations.

Overall, dining at The Pantry was a delightful experience that added a wonderful flavor to our Amsterdam adventure. name: Restaurant Olijfje
description:
OVER ONS
Bij mediterraan restaurant Olijfje wacht de liefhebbers van mals vlees, verse vis en overheerlijke wijnen een warme en typische mediterraan gastvrijheid. Tevens kunt u genieten van onze ijskoude Spaanse bier "Mahou" van de tap.
Restaurant Olijfje is niet zomaar een restaurant, maar een complete en onvergetelijke beleving in een sfeervolle ambiance. Bij Olijfje wordt de gast nog in de watten gelegd. Terwijl de chefkok de door u gekozen gerechten klaarmaakt op een echte houtskoolgrill en u culinair verrast, kunt u genieten van onze overheerlijke zelfgemaakte Spaanse tapas en de mediterrane mezes. Humus, tzatziki, bladerdeegrolletjes met Turkse feta kaas, de Griekse dolmas en de gepanneerde gamba's zullen uw tong strelen.

name: Black and Blue
description: Experience an unforgettable dining adventure at Black and Blue in Amsterdam. Nestled in the heart of the city center, this top-rated restaurant serves the finest local dishes with a gourmet twist. Savour succulent steaks, fresh lobster, and a variety of mouthwatering French cuisine. Whether you're seeking a cozy spot for lunch near Anne Frank's house or planning a fine-dining experience, Black and Blue is the perfect destination. Voted as one of the best restaurants in Amsterdam, it offers an exceptional dining atmosphere that will make your visit to this vibrant city all the more memorable. Make a reservation at Black and Blue today!

name: Loetje
description:
In hartje Amsterdam, tegenover Amsterdam Centraal Station, kun je in het vroegere Zuid-Hollandsch Koffiehuis, Loetje Amsterdam Centraal vinden. In ons monumentale pand, ingericht met Hollandse en Delftsblauwe accenten, kun je de lekkerste biefstuk van Amsterdam komen proeven!

Zeg je Loetje, dan zeg je de lekkerste biefstuk. Op no-nonsense wijze in echte Loetje Jus met witbrood, een royaal portie friet en salade. Bij ons geniet je van het vertrouwde biefstukreceptuur en het warme Loetje DNA.

Naast deze klassiekers hebben we bij Loetje Amsterdam Centraal nog veel meer lekkers op de kaart. Bij ons zit je ook goed voor vis, vegetarisch en overheerlijk toetjes. Zien we je snel?

Team Loetje

The waitress who served us seemed impatient with us after our mains were served and she must've been at the end of her shift since after a few leading queries about whether we were finished or not, she never returned and we had to hunt down an alternative waitress to pay the bill since no one was around except by the bar. Mind the restaurant was open for another two hours at the time we actually left. Perhaps it's a culture difference...

The food on the other hand was delicious. We had the tenderloin, fish, and a fried Thai-esque dish. Dessert was also delicious despite the passive rush for us to leave. The gentleman who delivered the panna cotta was very kind and enthusiastic about the desserts that were being delivered.

All in all, good food with mediocre service. name: Senses Restaurant
description:
Senses is a fine dining restaurant in the city center of Amsterdam where Chef Renaud Goigoux, Sous chefs Joao Marques let their inspiration and creativity into a chefs' menu inspired by Japanese cuisine, Dutch seasonality with a French flair.

Curating the best seasonal and sustainable products of the North-sea and Dutch soil, with a focus on vegetables and seafood. The team aims to deliver the best quality of food and service to their guests with the intention to bring awareness about sustainability.

Choose from the changing 2 to 5 course lunch or 3 to 6-course dinner Chef's menu. Be guided by the five senses and go on a journey of discovery.

name: Restaurant Bellezza
description: Bellezza, Divine Dining, will take you on a sensory journey that delights and inspires. You will discover the art of cuisine with a fine-dining menu created by chef Davy van Wezel. Every dish is a masterpiece of flavor and creativity. Bellezza is more than simply a restaurant serving exquisite food it is as much an artwork, an installation, an environment designed to make a meal into an event.

name: FuLu
description:
FuLu Mandarijn is one of the best restaurants in Amsterdam for lunch or dinner dining, thanks to our authentic Sichuan cuisine.

Chinese food can be savoured in the centre of Amsterdam, right next to Dam square, where we conjure up a wide extension of Asian food, creative desserts and signature cocktails.

Let's bring it on and enjoy the best Chinese restaurant in Amsterdam!

It was perfectly pan-fried with a crispy exterior and tender inside, coated in a sauce that was just incredible. The flavor was a perfect balance of sweet, sour, and slightly spicy, with so much depth--it was such a perfect match with rice that I finished a bowl in no time!

The seasonings are well-balanced, adding just the right amount of spiciness and flavor to make these beans a standout dish. The Stir-Fried Meat is thinly sliced and stir-fried with fresh vegetables and aromatic spices. It has a wonderful combination of textures, with the tender meat and the crunchy veggies, and a mouthwatering flavor that makes it a favorite among diners. The Kung Pao Chicken, paired with peanuts, dried chilies, and a tangy sauce, offer a perfect blend of sweet, spicy, and savory flavors. I come to Fulu every time to celebrate birthdays, festivals, and friends' graduations. I still remember the first time I came to Fulu for dinner was last winter. The academic pressure made me miss home, and my friend invited me to eat at Fulu. When I opened the door on the first floor, it was almost full of Chinese people, and the smell of Chinese food made me feel like I was back home. When I looked at the menu, I felt like I wanted to eat everythingAfter the dishes were served, everyone stopped talking and started to eat. I felt healed by the taste of home.
We ordered several dishes and I recommend the following ones:
-Dry pot shrimp: The shrimp meat is full and chewy, delicious and spicy 
-Spicy chicken: Very layered, crispy on the outside and tender on the inside, the taste of pepper makes me want to eat it unstoppably
-Fish-fragrant eggplant: Although I occasionally make it myself, I still ordered it. It is completely different from making it with flavor packets. It is unexpectedly delicious and really amazing to eat with rice
-Twice-cooked pork: The surface is shiny and slightly burnt. The meat is soft and chewy when eaten. It is fat but not greasy, lean but not dry. It is a must-order with friends every time
-Dry-fried green beans: After coming here, I found that green beans are difficult to fry and difficult to make it good taste. This green bean is perfect.
Because the restaurant is in the tourist area,  it's beside Dam square and it's at the exit of Rokin subway station, you can often see tourists coming to eat. It is really kind to see people from my motherland when I am away from homeThe waiters are also very thoughtful and attentive, and I am very happy every time I come. I think it's the best Chinese restaurant in Amsterdam. If you miss the food of your hometown, and if you want to taste authentic Chinese food, come here for a meal!","published_at":"2 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-11-05T19:53:43","response_from_owner_text":"Dear Carol J,

name: Cafe restaurant van Kerkwijk
description:
Van Kerkwijk is een klassiek Amsterdams cafe-restaurant.
Van Kerkwijk staat voor goed eten en drinken in een stadse sfeer.
Eigenzinnig, zonder kapsones voor een goede prijs.
Van Kerkwijk bestaat 20 jaar, nu met wat aanpassingen maar nog steeds persoonlijk en vertrouwd.

No menu, need to listen the staff to read the menu to you. Don't go there if your English or Dutch is not good as you will have problem for ordering. I don't know how do they serve customer having hearing problem. There is no where to list out the exact charge on food, drinks, service etc (they just give you a range). You only able to know it after getting the bill. But of cost you can request them to give you the total amount after ordering. name: Onze Zaak - Italiaans Restaurant
description: Onze Zaak is een Italiaans restaurant in het hart van Amsterdam, gelegen in de pittoreske Begijnensteeg. Geniet bij ons van een verfijnde lunch, een gezellige borrel of een sfeervol diner met authentieke Italiaanse gerechten. Chef Mattia Pedroni, met ervaring in toprestaurants in Londen en New York, bereidt dagelijks vers focaccia en ravioli volgens familierecept. Met een uitgebreide wijnkaart, zorgvuldig geselecteerde lokale en biologische producten, en een fijn terras, bieden wij een complete culinaire beleving. Kom langs en proef de sfeer van Onze Zaak!

name: de Silveren Spiegel
description:
AMSTERDAM'S FINEST RESTAURANT
A dining experience you will remember
Elegance, tradition and hospitality are the core traits of one of Amsterdam's finest restaurants, de Silveren Spiegel (the Silver Mirror). The restaurant dates from the Dutch Golden Age. A unique evening out in breathtaking surroundings befitting the likes of Rembrandt and Vermeer.

The restaurant has never been more renowned for its delicate approach to Fine Dutch cuisine, than under the present ownership of Familie van der Hoff. You may enjoy dinner here in the style of centuries of tradition and in tune with the cycles of the seasons. If you want to be sure that we can host you at the evening of your choice, please fill out our form on the website to make a reservation.

It is more than worth the price from the service and presentation, to the symphony of flavors with each bite.  My girlfriend and I had the seven-course dinner (which was essentially 12 different items) and ordered wine separately.

The dishes appear small, but they are the "Hermione's Purse" of flavor and satisfaction. Menu is attached. The one resting on a white, textured rhombus, I couldn't begin to describe. I have no ability to describe flavor--I'm sorry. But when I tell you I left my body for a moment, you MUST try this.

None of this meal disappointed. Trying to pick my least favorite dish feels unnecessary and difficult. It would be like trying to pick my least favorite song on a great artist's album. If you are in Amsterdam, you have to go to this restaurant.

The waitstaff was friendly, attentive, knowledgeable (and could make it graspable to a novice like me), and even gave history of the 17th century home that houses the restaurant.

I literally have zero critiques. Dates, small family or group (2-4 people) dinners, a deeper way to celebrate life, this special place is perfect for it all.

name: Pesca Vis Seafood Restaurant Amsterdam
description:
Dagelijks kraakverse vis in ons restaurant. De vismarkt bestaat uit een varierend seizoensaanbod. Alle oude regels zijn overboord gegooid: geen menu's of witte linnen. Het draait bij ons om de ervaring en versheid. Op de vismarkt kies jij zelf je verse vis zoals oesters, mosselen, zeebaars en meer! Ons Theatre of Fish voorziet elke visliefhebber van de lekkerste visgerechten. Gelegen op de Rozengracht in Amsterdam kan je naast kraakverse vis dineren, ook lunchen in het weekend! Overtuigd? Boek vandaag nog en sea you there!

Wij gaan bewust om met visvangst en hebben daarom de Pesca Foundation opgericht om bij te dragen aan duurzame visserij, gezonde visstand en een schone, plastic vrije oceaan.

name: Bleu
description: Discover exquisite dining at Restaurant Bleu, one of Amsterdam's top restaurants. Nestled in the charming Jordaan neighborhood, it is conveniently located near iconic landmarks like the Anne Frank House. This cozy restaurant is renowned for serving the best steaks in Amsterdam and is an unmissable spot for lobster lovers. From lunch to dinner, enjoy every meal with their wide-ranging French cuisine. Whether you're searching for a cafe, a food spot, or a restaurant near you in Amsterdam, Restaurant Bleu is an excellent choice. Experience the finest dining Amsterdam has to offer at this local gem.

Housed in a classic Amsterdam building, the restaurant exudes a cozy and inviting atmosphere.

The ambiance was delightful, and the staff were warm and welcoming. Seating is limited on the ground floor, and we climbed a steep, winding staircase to our reserved table on the second floor. While the restaurant was bustling, the service, though friendly, was notably slow.

For my main course, I ordered the Angus tenderloin, requesting it medium rare. Unfortunately, it arrived dry and closer to medium well. What I found particularly disappointing was that the steak did not come with a sauce. It had to be ordered separately--unlike my experiences in French restaurants. Instead, I had to pay extra for it, which felt odd. Dessert was a mixed experience--it was far too large, and the chocolate cake crumble was overpowering. Neither of us were able to finish it. A smaller, more balanced portion would have been preferable.

Despite these hiccups, we enjoyed a wonderful evening in good company. Bistro Bleu is worth a visit for its ambiance, though a few improvements could make the dining experience even better.","published_at":"a month ago","published_at_date":"2024-11-19T09:58:09","response_from_owner_text":"Hey there, Eliane Muskus! The food was amazing and the place was really lively, though we did start off a bit annoyed. But that didn't really spoil the whole fun evening.

On a busy Saturday night, I felt excited but also a bit mixed up. The bistro was full of energy, but we had a small problem at the start. We were sitting upstairs, kind of alone, and it took slightly more than 20 minutes just to get our drinks. This little mix-up was a bit of a letdown at first. And, trying to get a server's attention to order our food, even though they were close by, was a bit annoying.
It looked like people sitting downstairs got their orders faster.

As the night went on, any small issues we had at first were quickly forgotten because the food was just so good.

Starters
The scallops were amazing - cooked just right and came with a really tasty pillow of peas that was a nice surprise.
The smoked salmon on toast was simple but really well done, with great quality ingredients that all worked well together.

Main Courses
The French Fish Stew really stood out. It was a big, tasty mix of seafood, veggies, and a creamy sauce, and there was so much of it I couldn't even finish it all.
My partner had a Black Angus tenderloin that was just perfect - it looked great and tasted even better, especially with the peppery sauce that made it even more special.

Dessert
The Tarte Tatin with caramel ice cream was the perfect end to a great meal. It was just the right size for sharing.

Final Thoughts
Bistro Bleu really shows off how good food and drinks can be, all in a lively and pretty place.

The slow service at the start was a small hiccup, probably because they needed more staff. And if you want your food faster, sitting downstairs might be a good idea. But honestly, the quality of the food stands out on its own, regardless of the wait.

Bistro Bleu is definitely a place you should try, with each dish feeling like it was made with a lot of attention ","published_at":"10 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-02-25T10:10:35","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"review_likes_count":0,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":["https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipNTnRRvgcR2pHBldthFKdxLv-i99sxWcdYGPvjP=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipNhDe0bGirtLBzP9liT4uccvar12u1GP1aqNXxf=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipOhrWL4QeTwAsyXcYp85HniIW0MsElczgcUEjh6=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipNdx1M_JmlnUU9Zr2b-eYN7p5J6HjTy3-Z6BfZ_=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipNriVxbFhb_ut5bpZfPTnyYfVO36djfQWMduGOC=s1024"]},{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNmaGIzbWdRRRAB","rating":2,"name":"Rich Gollinge","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102121155104326895798?hl=en-GB","review_text":"We walked in and smelled sewage. Should have turned around, but we didn't have reservations anywhere else, so we stuck it out. We ordered smoked salmon on toast, "French" onion soup, steak tartare and the signature Bleu salad with grilled chicken. Oh boy, where to begin? The soup.. bland, flat, devoid of any flavor. The stock seemed to be chicken, maybe they dunked a chicken in hot tap water and boiled onions in it to call it soup. Smoked salmon on sourdough toast was also lacking in flavor, no presentation, but at least my wife got some protein. The salad was decent, fresh mesclun greens with half a hard boiled egg, house made vinaigrette.. But the chicken- was not only NOT grilled, it tasted like 2 day old baked baked chicken thigh uncovered in the fridge, then reheated for the salad. Steak tartare- well at least it was ground beef. However, it did not have the traditional encoutrements, and was served with white bread toast that was grilled. We spent nearly 100 Euros on this and to be honest, it was the worst meal we ate in Amsterdam. A 100 Euro meal should taste like one. I'm a chef and normally I like to recommend restaurants, but I just can't in this case.","published_at":"2 weeks ago","published_at_date":"2024-12-30T22:09:45","response_from_owner_text":"Rich Gollinge, we're deeply sorry to hear about your disappointing experience at Restaurant Bleu. name: Ashoka
description:
Fine Dining with a Refined Concept
**********************
Serving the finest Indian and Nepalese cuisines since 2013, Ashoka is ranked as one of the best restaurants in Amsterdam.

Refined service paired with caring, gracious hospitality, and soulful Indian and Nepalese cuisines at a fair price in a cozy and beautiful restaurant in the heart of Amsterdam. Enjoy and experience the amazing flavors of India and Nepal in our one-of-a-kind restaurant built in the monument warehouse.

Located in the historical heart of the city, Ashoka is just a stone's throw away from Amsterdam Central Station. Famous Dam Square and Amsterdam's leading department store De Bijenkorf are within walking distance; just 600 meters from our doorstep.

[{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNQaEx5YXd3RRAB","rating":5,"name":"Rayan Alwabil","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104512169807719286736?hl=en-GB","review_text":"My wife and I recently had the pleasure of dining at Ashoka, and I can honestly say it was an unforgettable experience from start to finish. We booked in advance, excited to try their renowned cuisine, and were immediately impressed by the elegant ambiance of the restaurant. The decor perfectly sets the stage for a delightful evening.

We opted for the chef's tasting menu for two, and it was nothing short of amazing. Each course was thoughtfully prepared and beautifully presented, showcasing the best dishes that Ashoka has to offer. The portions were just right, allowing us to savor each flavor without feeling overwhelmed.

Among the standout dishes, the butter chicken was a true highlight. Rich and creamy, it was bursting with flavor--definitely one of the best I've ever had. We also loved the masala, which was perfectly spiced and complemented the other dishes beautifully. Every bite was a celebration of Indian cuisine, and the variety in the tasting plate kept our taste buds excited.

What truly enhanced our experience was the exceptional service. The staff were not only helpful but also genuinely friendly. They were attentive without being intrusive, making sure our dining experience was seamless and enjoyable.

Overall, our evening at Ashoka was a wonderful culinary journey that we will be talking about for a long time. We can't wait to return and explore more of their delicious offerings. Highly recommend this restaurant to anyone looking for a top-notch dining experience!","published_at":"a month ago","published_at_date":"2024-11-21T13:05:20","response_from_owner_text":"Hello. Namaste Rayan,
We are delighted that you have chosen to dine with us! We appreciate your positive feedback and look forward to continuing to provide exceptional service.

We started with the appetisers, which were decent but didn't stand out much in terms of flavour. We had Chicken Choila and Chicken Momo. The Momo were a bit of a disappointment, as they were served cold. We were expecting them to be at least warm, considering how they're typically enjoyed fresh, but they missed the mark in that regard.

However, the main course more than made up for it. The Kukhura Ko Masu (traditional Nepalese chicken curry) was absolutely on point. The flavour was rich, and well-seasoned. It was the highlight of the meal, and we really enjoyed it. It came with rice by default, and we added an extra garlic naan, which was delicious, warm, and perfectly complementing the curry.

What really made the experience stand out was the service. The staff was exceptionally friendly, attentive, and accommodating, which made us feel very welcome throughout our meal. They were definitely a big part of the positive experience.

name: Blue Amsterdam
description:
Blue Amsterdam is the place to be in the city centre for breakfast, lunch, coffee and cakes, beers and snacks and home made lemonades with an amazing panoramic view of the city. Explore the city, start at Blue. Just walk in!
We hope to welcome you soon!

The view alone makes it worth a visit, especially if you're looking for a unique spot to enjoy your meal.

The breakfast menu is fairly priced, and the food was not only absolutely delicious but also came in portions that felt very reasonable for the price. While individual items might seem a bit more expensive, the quality of the food and the overall experience more than justify the cost.

The cafe can get quite busy, and the space is relatively small, spread across two floors, but that didn't bother me too much--it added to the cozy atmosphere. The staff were incredibly attentive, friendly, and just genuinely kind, which made the visit even more enjoyable.

name: Bistrot Neuf
description: Neuf is een authentiek Frans restaurant gelegen op de bruisende Haarlemmerstraat, aan de rand van de nostalgische Jordaan in Amsterdam. Neuf staat voor ongecompliceerd en lekker eten, met als basis wijn. We serveren 7 dagen per week (warme) lunch en diner en alle gerechten worden in eigen huis bereid. Kies een van onze heerlijke a la carte gerechten of laat je verrassen door de Chef in de vorm van een 3-, 4- of 5 gangen Chefs Tasting Menu. De warme keuken is iedere dag vanaf 12:00 uur geopend voor lunch (tot 16:30 uur) en voor diner vanaf 17:30 uur tot 22:00 uur.

[{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUM3ektQbm5BRRAB","rating":5,"name":"Joyce Cui","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102014493075194455946?hl=en-GB","review_text":"Our experience here on Aug 11 was 10 out of 10. We were able to book a table for Friday evening the day before. When we arrived we were greeted in a friendly way and given a nice table. After about 10 minutes the sommelier, asked if we wanted to see the wine menu, but we were not given the food menu's. So we decided to just have a glass of wine, since we had no idea what we were going to be eating. I further found the way that the sommelier acted was a bit arrogant and patronising. I can maybe understand it if he would be working in a 3 Michelin star restaurant, but not in a bistro.. The food was fine, bouillabaisse, tartare de boeuf and goose liver for starter were fine. We decided to have the special of the day, which was a beef Wellington for two. As it was for two, I expected it to be a small Wellington or similar, but I was surprised when they just served two slices of Wellington on a plate. Why did this have to be ordered for two people? It came with some salad and fries. The beef was nicely cooked, but the pastry was very soggy and for some reason they had wrapped the inside layer (which I assume was a crepe) with lettuce leaves, which was a first for me in a Wellington. So I was not blown away, and my son told me he preferred the Wellington I make at home.. My wife's bouillabaisse was fine. She did throw up all night, but we are not sure what caused that, and as I had the same thing as a starter and I had no issues, I don't think it was the bouillabaisse. name: BREDA
description:
In onze zaak, Restaurant BREDA, krijgt het Bourgondische leven van onze geboortestad hoofdstedelijke allure. Een moderne internationale keuken op hoog niveau, in een warme en toegankelijke entourage.
Met een menu van de chef en een wijnkaart, die op zichzelf al een bezoek waard is, hopen we u te mogen verwelkomen voor lunch en diner aan het Singel 210.

name: Kaap & Tein
description:
STADSHAVEN - Restaurant met gezellige bar en terras.

KAAP/Tein heeft het beste van twee (onder)werelden. Bepaal je koers en KAAP je plekje aan de Zeedijk of laat je verleiden door het baken van licht aan de Geldersekade.

name: Restaurant La Cantina
description: One of the few truly authentic Italian restaurants in the Amsterdam city center. If you want to experience a genuine Italian family feast there's nothing quite like La Cantina. Our Italian chefs will offer you a choice of both classic, traditional dishes and fine dining specialties. So please join us for a true Mediterranean experience in our cozy restaurant or, whether permitting, sit outside on our lovely terrace and enjoy one of our lunch specials or a romantic dinner.

name: Eetcafe 't Pakhuis
description:
Wij zijn een gezellig eetcafe in het centum van Amsterdam. Bij ons kan iedereen genieten van een brunch, lunch of diner.
Wij serveren diverse gerechten en voor ieder wat wils. Ook hebben wij vegetarische gerechten en houden wij rekening met allergieen.

name: Bussia
description:
Our kitchen has a refined Italian style of cooking, where classic taste and scent combinations are given a modern, international twist. The pasta, bread and pastries are all made on the premises, and all of our dishes are prepared with daily fresh, rustic ingredients.
Located in the charming '9 Streets', amongst the beautiful canals of Amsterdam, the open kitchen and mezzanine level create a special atmosphere of convivial comfort, where your dining experience is enhanced by attentive and knowledgeable service.
We look forward to welcoming you at Bussia.

name: Frenzi Italian Restaurant
description: Welcome to Frenzi, a cosy Italian restaurant in the centre of Amsterdam. Located in one of the city's most picturesque spots with stunning canal views, Frenzi is the perfect destination for lovers of fresh, authentic Italian cuisine. Indulge in our expertly crafted dishes, from handmade pastas to wood-fired pizzas, all made with the finest ingredients to delight even the most refined palates. Whether you're enjoying lunch, dinner, or drinks, our warm and inviting atmosphere sets the stage for unforgettable shared moments. Discover Italian dining at its best in Amsterdam. Let Frenzi surprise you - visit us today!

name: La Casa di Angelo Amsterdam
description: Italy is closer than you think, La Casa di Angelo is a good example of this. Taste the real Italian food and dine in a Mediterranean and lively atmosphere. There is a large choice of authentic Italian specialties, but the traditional pizzas and pastas are also on the menu. The sunny, southern decor and the friendly service ensure a successful Italian evening.

name: Morlang Cafe Restaurant Amsterdam
description:
Discover Morlang Cafe Restaurant Amsterdam, for over 40 years we've been the ultimate destination for every occasion in the heart of Amsterdam Center on the iconic Keizersgracht. Whether you're in the mood for a leisurely Breakfast, a delightful Lunch, or a cozy Dinner,
Our Restaurant offers spacious interiors perfect for intimate meals, lively gatherings, or hosting unforgettable private dining events. On sunny days, our big terrace becomes the go-to spot for enjoying a meal or drink with stunning canal views.

Besides our Restaurant guests can enjoy a coffee in our cafe or a fine selection of cocktails, wines and beers in our bar. We also cater to business events, making it the ideal location for any occasion.

Your table awaits!

The restaurant offers a variety of well-cooked steaks, with the Lomito being a popular choice among patrons.

The steak quality is very good, and the meat is cooked to perfection. The location is convenient, being close to Dam Square, which makes it an easy choice for tourists exploring the area. The staff is friendly, adding to the positive dining experience.

However, the restaurant's setting is quite simple, with basic chairs and tables. It's not a fancy place, so don't expect a luxurious ambiance. Steaks are served on their own, and you need to order sides separately. While some might prefer this, it can be a downside for those who expect a complete meal without additional charges. Additionally, the staff, while friendly, can be a bit slow, which might affect the overall dining experience.

Overall, CAU Steak Restaurant is a great choice for those looking to enjoy good steak near Dam Square. Despite its simplicity and a few drawbacks, the quality of the food makes it worth a visit.","published_at":"6 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-06-30T20:04:34","response_from_owner_text":"Hi Ziv,

name: Beers & Barrels Amsterdam
description:
Welkom bij Beers & Barrels.

Met maar liefst 78 verschillende bieren, taptafels en heerlijke gerechten is Beers & Barrels the place to be. Geniet van onze Dry Age specials of andere gerechten die bereid worden op de Josper grill. Neem samen met vrienden, familie of collega's plaats aan een van onze taptafels met eigen tapkraan. Want niets smaakt zo goed als een zelfgetapt biertje. Perfect voor een onvergetelijke middag of avond. Maar ook voor een avond lekker dansen kun je bij Beers & Barrels terecht. Raise your glass at Beers & Barrels en begin jouw weekend extra lekker met ambachtelijke gerechten, bieren, verrassende cocktails en live muziek.
Maak snel je reservering bij Beers & Barrels of kom spontaan langs.

Team Beers & Barrels.

I recently visited this restaurant with my family, drawn by the promise of excellent food, which I must say truly lived up to expectations. The dishes were delicious, and it's clear the chefs put a lot of care and skill into their work. Hats off to them for creating such a memorable culinary experience!

However, the overall experience was unfortunately marred by the service. We made a reservation for 9:00 PM, but just ten minutes after we arrived, we were told by the waiter that we needed to order immediately as the kitchen was closing. This was surprising, as we had reserved well in advance and received no prior notice of the kitchen's early closing. It left us feeling rushed and questioning the purpose of our reservation time.

The service also lacked a touch of professionalism. Our waiter brought cutlery to our table but placed it in the middle without distributing it, unlike the attention given to other tables nearby. Furthermore, when a small accident occurred and water was spilled on me, the waiter simply smiled without an apology, which felt dismissive and unprofessional.

While the food is truly excellent and worth coming back for, the inconsistency in service creates an unfortunate imbalance. I would recommend the restaurant to those who value great cuisine, but I hope the management considers improvements in staff training to better reflect the quality of the kitchen.","published_at":"2 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-10-31T01:34:43","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"review_likes_count":0,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":[]},{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURuLWJDZm1RRRAB","rating":5,"name":"Marc Davison","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107529951043714339563?hl=en-GB","review_text":"Superb meal. [{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNuM2E3RjlBRRAB","rating":2,"name":"hussain marafie","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102456789866252018417?hl=en-GB","review_text":"Lebanese Restaurant.

I can say that nothing especial in the restaurant & over rated in google by 4.5!

The only advantage I believe that they don't have another Lebanese restaurant to compete with them in Amsterdam.

Food is acceptable especially the normal oven bread, we like it but the shish tawoq and falafel  are very normal.

The staff are moody and somehow friendly, when they noticed that we are from Kuwait with a baby they treat us differently .

They are really expensive compared to other Arabic restaurants in Amsterdam, average per person 25-35 Euros!

Overall I can rate the experience by 2.5, maximum 3 out of 5.

name: Restaurant Black
description: Discover the culinary gem that is Restaurant Black, nestled in the vibrant heart of Amsterdam city center. Serving the best breakfast, lunch, and dinner near you, it's a must-visit spot for food-lovers. Looking for the best steak in Amsterdam? Your search ends at the doors of Restaurant Black. We also specialize in fine dining, offering an exquisite Lobster experience that will tantalize your taste buds. Located in the bustling Leidseplein, we're not just another restaurant - we're the best restaurant in Amsterdam. So whether you're craving a hearty breakfast, a leisurely lunch, or a decadent dinner, Restaurant Black has got you covered.

[{"review_id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUR2OGQ3NUl3EAE","rating":4,"name":"Sharon","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115547415524934380166?hl=en-GB","review_text":"It was a cold day, so we stopped here for lunch.  We waited to be seated, not sure what conversation the staff were having in the restaurant, but it took a while to be seated.

We also had to wait to be given menus. We ordered an apple juice and a beer for food I had the grilled chicken sandwich on focaccia bread and my husband had the two croquettes on bread with mustard sauce. We didn't wait long for the food to arrive. The portions are large, you wouldn't need any extras with them. All freshly done and taste very nice.

name: Restaurant Red
description: Discover the tantalising flavours of the best steak in Amsterdam at Restaurant RED. Gourmet steak lovers, our premium steakhouse provides a dining experience like no other. From succulent ribeye steak to a variety of steak meals, our menu is a carnivore's dream. Not only do we excel at steak, but we're also well-renowned as a top lobster and fish restaurant in Amsterdam. Situated near the historic Rijksmuseum, whether you're looking for breakfast, lunch, dinner, or a canal-side diner, Restaurant RED is the place to be. We promise a dining experience that will keep you coming back for more. Choose Restaurant RED for the ultimate Amsterdam steakhouse experience.

name: Restaurant Ava Cyril
description:
Restaurant Ava Cyril
Italiaans in het epicentrum van Amsterdam
===============================
Ava Cyril is een Italiaans steak- en pizza restaurant met zoveel kleur en sfeer dat je gelijk thuis voelt. De muren hangen vol met bankbiljetten uit vreemde landen, bierviltjes beschreven met aardige woorden en sfeerlicht. Een betaalbare plek in het epicentrum van de Amsterdamse vakantieganger!
================================
Cozy restaurant with an open kitchen in the center of amsterdam, very close to central station, our concept: customer is part of our family, we do our food with love, we got a decent food for a reasonable price.

We are doing our best to provide our guests with excellent and fast service, while communicating in advance in case of some waiting time, because of our many orders.

We hope to see you again in any of our locations and offer you this 5-star  experience we are striving for!

name: Restaurant Hulscher's
description: Twee broers met totaal tegenstrijdige karakters en toch een en dezelfde missie: De wereld veroveren met hun passie voor lekker eten! De historische tempel van Restaurant Hulscher's staat dan ook geheel in het teken van deze contrasten, maar vooral van de onweerstaanbare vlees of visgerechten en natuurlijk de wereldberoemde genummerde biefstuk met uitsluitend verse en eigengemaakte ingredienten. Vlees of vis? Zoals mevrouw Hulscher het aan de vooravond van dit meer dan honderdjaar oude Amsterdamse succesverhaal al voorspelde: "The best of both worlds."

Located in Amsterdam Centre nearby Carre, the National Holocaust Memorial of Names, The Hermitage, The Hortus Botanicus Amsterdam, City Zoo Artis and National Opera & Ballet (Stopera).

The establishment is known for its friendly service, cozy atmosphere, and a menu that caters to various dietary preferences, including vegan and vegetarian options.

One of the standout features of Petit Lou is its live music events. On the last Sunday of each month, the brasserie hosts jazz jam sessions featuring talented musicians. For instance, the "Theo Naishtat Quartet" has performed, providing an evening of captivating jazz music that enhances the dining experience. These sessions typically start around 18:30, followed by an open jam session where patrons can enjoy spontaneous performances.

The combination of excellent food, attentive staff, and live jazz music makes Petit Lou a must-visit spot in Amsterdam. name: PRESSROOM Amsterdam
description: PRESSROOM Amsterdam is a restaurant located in the heart of Amsterdam with a story. Not just any story; the first page dates back to 1904 when our building became the base of Dutch newspaper 'De Tijd'. With a history like that, it's no surprise PRESSROOM is still a place ''where stories are yet to be written''. Today, this rich history is translated into a relaxed experience with a modern and personal approach. In 2023, PRESSROOM has been awarded with three awards concerning the cuisine and the design of the restaurant. PRESSROOM lives from early morning until late at night simply because the story must go on. The menu consists of modern classics with local ingredients and tasteful flavors that merge into perfect combinations on your plate.

name: Burger Bar
description:
Burgerbar features not only fresh and homemade sauces, toppings and bread, but also fresh beef ground daily in our own production kitchen. We choose to work only with the best quality beef whilst offering three types in order to satisfy even the most refined palates; Irish, Angus and Wagyu beef. Come and try The Real Bite!
*Please note that our kitchen closes 30 minutes before the restaurant's closing time.*

name: The Lebanese Sajeria Utrechtsestraat
description:
"The Lebanese Sajeria has been serving up fresh (literally and figuratively!) takes on Lebanese classics since 2015, when we brought a saj* over from Lebanon. We first started selling our signature manousheh* at food markets around Amsterdam, then out of a food-truck window as we toured the country. Today, we have four of our very own counters across the city."

Vegan , vegetarian, meat and gluten free options available !

PLEASE NOTE THAT LAST SEATING IS 30 MINUTES BEFORE CLOSING TIME!

The interior is minimalistic but the branding is very cool. All in black and white, which comic sketches on the wall that illustrate the story of the restaurant chain. (There are locations in the city center and now also in Noord)
The Menu relies on Manousheh (Lebanese wraps) and a selection of sides and soups.
They also offer the soup on larger quantities for you to keep in your freezer for later.
The Manousheh come with beef, chicken or lamb, veggie and vegan options. So
There is literally something for everyone. I had the Haloumi Zataar and my boyfriend had the beef and Labneh. Both were delicious! Super authentic and very filling.
Staff is friendly and the food was there in no time. I also had a ginger lemonade on the side which was very good.
I will definitely come back and try the lentil soup and the hummus. 10/10!","published_at":"2 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-11-10T10:48:34","response_from_owner_text":"Hello Alina,

description: 100% Plant-based & FairTrade, mostly organic, with team Margo's serving up classic homemade french pastries for breakfast, artisan American style submarine sandwiches in her freshly baked bread for lunch, and speciality premium coffee all day long! name: Restaurant Argentalia Amsterdam
description:
Argentalia is a fusion restaurant, a unique culinary blend of the flavorful traditions of Italy and Argentina. Located in the city's heart, we take our patrons on a gastronomic journey, merging the rustic charm of Argentine food with the subtlety of Italian gastronomy.

Our menu is centered around fresh ingredients and authentic recipes. It embodies the hearty Argentine flavors famous for its robust meats, with Italy's rich heritage of fresh pasta, aromatic sauces, and divine cheese and wine.
Argentalia's aesthetic reflects its menu - a beautiful amalgamation of rustic Argentine warmth and timeless Italian elegance.

name: Lotti's
description:
Lotti's is a modern European restaurant celebrating seasonality and Dutch ingredients in a welcoming all-day setting. Whether you're craving good, honest food without the fuss or a locally inspired beverage, Lotti's is the place to be.

The menu has something for everyone, from Dutch favorites and lighter bites to comforting dishes and hearty plates perfect for evening dining.

name: Bistro Berlage
description: Gezellige Bistro op loopafstand van het Centraal Station van Amsterdam. Heerlijke lokale gerechten tijdens de lunch of diner, maar ook een geweldige plek om te borrelen na een dag shoppen in Amsterdam. Goed te combineren met een escape room van Sherlocked of een bezoek aan Tony's Chocolonely super store.

name: O MAI
description: Vietnamese restaurant located at Rembrandtsplein. We serve quick meals or dining experiences from up to 90 minutes. Come in by yourself, with a date or a mate and otherwise with groups up to 32 people. Well behaved dogs are allowed. We cater to meat lovers and have some options for vegetarians and vegans. So if you crave pho, hu tieu, bun or banh mi, then O MAI is the place for you to be.

name: Box Sociaal
description:
Nestled in the heart of Amsterdam, Box Sociaal converges the spirit of community and Aussie dining. Inspired by rich traditions from the early 1900s, our restaurant offers a modern Australian cuisine experience with a focus on delectable brunches and cocktails.
Enjoy a diverse menu featuring Aussie-style breakfasts, eggs Benedict, and fluffy pancakes, or explore our health-conscious options like gluten-free dishes and vegetarian delights including shakshuka. Our bar serves up meticulously crafted cocktails, natural wines, and local beers, perfect for any occasion from cheeky mimosas at breakfast to bottomless brunch.

We also cater for private functions including corporate events birthdays, events and engagements. Come celebrate with us!

name: Brasserie Ambassade
description:
Kom binnen voor een heerlijk ontbijt, lunch of diner bij Brasserie Ambassade - onderdeel van het Ambassade Hotel - gelegen aan de Herengracht in het centrum van Amsterdam. Geniet van de Franse keuken met een moderne twist terwijl je omringd wordt door kleurrijke schilderijen van bekende CoBrA kunstenaars. Of neem in de zomer plaats op ons terras met uitzicht op de gracht!

Bij Brasserie Ambassade ligt de nadruk op verse, seizoensgebonden, ambachtelijke en lokale producten. De keuken van Brasserie Ambassade biedt een heerlijk en veelzijdig a la carte menu en wijnkaart.
Het team van Brasserie Ambassade verwelkomt u graag!

name: Bollywood Indian Restaurant
description: Embark on a flavorful journey at Restaurant Bollywood, where each dish narrates a tale of India's rich culinary heritage. Nestled in Amsterdam, our vibrant establishment promises an unforgettable dining experience inspired by Bollywood. From classic curries to innovative fusion creations, our menu celebrates aromatic spices and hearty flavors. We also offer a delightful selection of vegan options, ensuring everyone can partake in the feast. With warm hospitality and personalized recommendations, our dedicated staff ensures every guest feels like a star. Join us to indulge in the magic of Bollywood at Restaurant Bollywood.

name: Hannekes Boom
description: Discover Hannekes Boom, a vibrant restaurant in Amsterdam that perfectly blends delicious food and a stunning waterfront view. Located near the Scheepvaartmuseum and Central Station, it's an ideal spot for lunch, dinner, or casual drinks. Enjoy our diverse menu featuring classic foods, craft beers and cocktails. Whether you're looking to relax on our terrace or enjoy a cozy meal inside, Hannekes Boom is your go-to restaurant for an unforgettable dining experience. Perfect for those searching for "restaurants near me" or "uiteten in Amsterdam." Join us for a taste of Amsterdam!

name: Kapitein Zeppos
description:
Kapitein Zeppos en is vernoemd naar de gelijknamige Vlaamse tv-serie uit de jaren '60 Zeppos bevindt zich in het pittoreske steegje 'Gebed zonder End'. Een verborgen parel in het centrum van Amsterdam, op 100 meter loopafstand van metro Rokin, uitgang Spui. Zeppos is vakantie in eigen land mede door zijn zuidelijke uitstraling. Je waant je in Italie of Spanje als je het Gebed in loopt!
Zeppos biedt nog veel meer, dan alleen genieten van onze zuidelijke gerechten en onze heerlijke biertjes, wijnen en cocktails. Er zit veel muziek in Zeppos. Wij verhuren twee prachtige zalen voor uw festiviteiten en organiseren prachtige voorstellingen in ons kleine theatertje, Claire's Ballroom. En je kan zelfs bij ons trouwen!

name: WE ARE EDN
description: Step into a vibrant dining experience at WE ARE EDN, a restaurant near Amsterdam Centraal. Rooted in nature, this all-day dining spot features a menu brimming with the freshest seasonal ingredients. From breakfast classics to lunch favorites, hearty burgers, pizza, pasta, and perfectly grilled steaks, there's something for everyone to enjoy. As an Amsterdam family restaurant, we offer a wide range of vegan, vegetarian, meat, and seafood options, catering to every taste. With a commitment to eco-friendly dining, each dish is crafted with sustainability in mind, making it the ideal choice for those who care about both great food and the planet. For an unforgettable all-day dining in Amsterdam, WE ARE EDN is the place you won't want to miss.

[{"review_id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUMzbzgzaFBREAE","rating":5,"name":"Terri Tratch","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117896528553289105823?hl=en-GB","review_text":"On our first night when visiting Amsterdam, we had dinner at the EDN and subsequently had all our meals there during the entire stay. The food was amazing, the best beef tartar I ever tried. Ceviche was amazing  and Sea Bass was also exceptional. Paulo one of our waiters was personable, gave us great recommendations, and was very pleasant to chat with it. The service at the restaurant is top-notch with the focus on great customer service and great food. Kudos to the entire team!","published_at":"2 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-11-08T18:04:16","response_from_owner_text":"Hi Terri,
 
Thank you so much for taking the time to share such  review! We're thrilled to hear that WE ARE EDN became your dining choice throughout your entire stay in Amsterdam.

It's fantastic to know that you enjoyed the dishes, especially the beef tartare, ceviche, and sea bass. Our chefs take great pride in creating memorable culinary experiences, and your kind words truly mean a lot. We're also delighted that Paulo made such a positive impression! Shortly after, a staff member loudly shouted "EXCUSE ME!!" to pass by with a dessert tray. Another employee eventually came to seat us. We asked for water while deciding on our drinks, but it didn't arrive until we asked again. Our Prosecco and water were finally brought out together, but the Prosecco was just below room temperature. We requested ice for our ice bucket, which was promptly provided.

Our starter, a prawn salad priced at EU15.50, was disappointingly small and tasted ok. However, the main course was visually appealing, with four prawns and a generous amount of tasty sauce. The staff appeared to be doing their best but clearly lacked proper training from the management. The ambiance was delightful, maintaining a beautiful, timeless charm.

name: Kitchen & Bar Van Rijn B.V.
description: Kitchen & Bar Van Rijn is gelegen aan het Rembrandtplein in Amsterdam en is geinspireerd door de schoonheid en de meesterwerken van Rembrandt van Rijn. In een kosmopolitische sfeer met open keuken kunnen de gasten genieten van een lunch en diner. In het weekend is er live muziek en ook een DJ. Kortom Kitchen & Bar Van Rijn is de ultieme locatie voor een heerlijke lunch of diner, kopje koffie op het terras en 's avonds gezellig met vrienden te borrelen.

We stepped inside, the vibe was grand,
A cozy nook, a well-set stand.
The music played, the lights were low,
A place where charm began to show.

The food was decent, plates well made,
A feast of flavors, well displayed.
But oh, the wait--so long, so grim,
Our patience wore excessively thin.

The staff, though kind, were lost in space,
With every glance, a missing face.
We asked, we waved, but no reply,
Just empty stares as time flew by.

And then, the sting--our sweet delight,
The promised dessert, a tragic plight.
Forgotten, missed, it never came,
A bitter note to end the game.

So here's the truth, the honest view,
A place of charm, but troubles too.
Decent food and a lovely scene,
But service slow--if you're not keen.","published_at":"a month ago","published_at_date":"2024-12-07T22:03:58","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"review_likes_count":0,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":[]},{"review_id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURIMmFTWFl3EAE","rating":3,"name":"Rupert Brun","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116781561523108424070?hl=en-GB","review_text":"I was there for a corporate hospitality event upstairs in the bar. Work done, body frozen, treat required. Behold! Opposite the Bijenkorf right on Dam Square, Royal 98. I'd never been before and I was actually heading somewhere else, or at least I thought I was, but then I caught sight of a flash of irresistible gezelligheid and I was in.

Inside I was greeted, given a choice of tables and accommodated in a timely and professional fashion. Warmhearted but not overbearing. Just right.

The menu was delivered. I perused and made my choice. Pappardelle beef ragu. House red.

From my high table at the back of the front section of the restaurant, I could see out across Dam Square, so twinkling and beautiful and Christmassy that you can just about convince yourself the world isn't really ending. Ditto Claudia Cardinale, on the wall to my left.

My wine came. And it was good.

Then my pasta came. And it was excellent. Succulent beef. Toothsome pasta ribbons. Damn near perfect. Made me feel guilty in all kinds of ways.

Then I noticed one of a nearby party of Germans order an Irish coffee and I had to have one. I also saw that there was a ten-euro tiramisu on the menu. And I had to have it. To say both were excellent would be an understatement. The tiramisu was one of the best I've ever had. The textures were ... almost moving. I could have eaten it a hundred times. Even the little sprig of mint was a triumph.

The staff too, were excellent. Two guys, Hans and Robert. Dutch guys! Dutch service is frequently diabolical but these guys were outstanding. As the restaurant became busy, they wordlessly catered to every table, every group, quickly, efficiently, and with genuine alacrity. There was one moment as they were pottering away behind the bar, that they started laughing together, and I liked that very much. Happy staff, doing a job they clearly enjoy and consequently doing it very well indeed.

Maybe I got lucky. I mean, I definitely got lucky because I can't think of a single weak point. It's not cheap, but of course it's not -- look where it is. But it's worth it. I didn't begrudge a penny. The decor is also great and supergezellig and there was a pretty decent Christmas soundtrack playing throughout.

I'm not exaggerating when I say this was one of my favourite Amsterdam dining experiences and I will remember it for the rest of my life. It's personal, you know? It just hit the right spot, in the right moment, and everything was perfect.

Wholeheartedly recommend.","published_at":"a month ago","published_at_date":"2024-12-10T13:40:49","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"review_likes_count":0,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":["https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipMpTphaS-GMUy_IwCnEEQ5ndJVC2y_oIGHyeufS=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipNqKnMgtdJLcnE7wDaVMELzfzYnxPkkMQ6oy0ih=s1024"]},{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUN6NEppSzVRRRAB","rating":4,"name":"Abdulrahman Alzamil (Zamil)","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111555237844996092010?hl=en-GB","review_text":"My experience at this restaurant in Amsterdam was fantastic! I had the fish and chips and my wife had the burger--both were very good (along with the beers!) and the staff was helpful and attentive.

As I said above, the only negative was the length of time to receive our main courses, about 1 hour.

I had seen another couple receive the same order we had (fish and chips, burger) and after about an hour, I was about to ask the staff about our order but before I could, our order was brought out to us.  The food was very tasty and piping hot so it was freshly prepared.

Even though we were eating well before the normal dinner time, it could have been just a surge of customers.  There were empty tables when we arrived but the place was packed when we left.

name: indian restaurant gandhi
description: Indian Restaurant Gandhi, the best Indian Restaurant located in the heart of Amsterdam's Centrum, has been delighting lunch and diners with authentic Indian flavours for over 23 years. Our extensive menu, inspired by India's rich culinary heritage, features mouth-watering dishes crafted with fresh ingredients and aromatic spices. Perfect for any occasion, we offer a range of services including lunch, dine-in, kerbside pickup, and convenient delivery options. Ordering online is a breeze, allowing you to enjoy our vibrant flavours from the comfort of your home. Whether you're craving a comforting curry or a spicy tandoori dish, Gandhi promises an unforgettable dining experience. Reserve or Orde online now!

I rarely leave negative reviews, but my experience at Gandhi Restaurant was so poor that I feel compelled to share. From the moment I walked in, the service was inattentive and cold. The staff seemed uninterested in even acknowledging us as we waited for our table, and once seated, we were ignored for long stretches of time. When we finally placed our order, it felt like an inconvenience to the waiter.

As for the food, it was absolutely terrible. The flavors were bland and completely lacked the richness and depth you'd expect from Indian cuisine. The curry I ordered was watery and tasteless, and the naan was dry and hard. The portions were tiny, especially considering the high prices. I've had far better Indian food at local takeout spots, which is saying a lot.

I was hoping for a great meal and a warm experience, but unfortunately, this place failed on both fronts. I won't be returning, and I strongly advise others to look elsewhere for authentic, flavorful Indian food in Amsterdam.","published_at":"2 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-11-13T22:28:31","response_from_owner_text":"Thank you Karim Shaikh for taking the time to share your feedback. Cozy and intimate restaurant with classic french atmosphere and refined food.

I'd recommend it for a romantic or celebratory evening, but food may be better elsewhere if you have a lot of vegetarians in the party.

Review:
I came here with 4 coworkers and we pretty much had the whole menu. I loved the atmosphere and overall vibe, I immediately felt like we were in a fancy legacy french restaurant.

I liked everything I tried, even the pate which I tend to not care for. I mean I didn't love it, but the subtle twists and overall quality made something I tend not to like into something I'd eat again! I was also pleasantly surprised to see my favorite wine on the menu.

Definitely the meat dishes are the draw. Most are served with great crusty bread. Few bites of food are as satisfying as fatty and creamy bone marrow over chewy crunchy bread.

I liked the fish dishes and I had a vegetarian dish was well, but I was most impressed with the meat dishes. My favorites were the pate, the bone marrow, and the pork head.","published_at":"10 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-02-18T17:27:14","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"review_likes_count":2,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":["https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipPA7gE-LOP4MywifFlvnxzye7Vg9frMU1YYCnEh=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipMivQNNozzvsYO7Mnopo4WlsB8ohf7pIaa9YdBR=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipMeXhAbcOK_3_GDGuUAmF-4Ig2s4zX4QCFRlA9c=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipOzgtm-7If0oFvUAmacHDYDHttSB6i078FU3Yy7=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipN7PDAZNhJI6gMHegfKvKFTKjrhAbuPRfrtS0Yy=s1024"]}]

We were blown away with the quality of our meal. The meat fell apart. In fact everyone's food in this little place looked appetising.
The lemongrass beef stew was delicately fragrant and light. The pork chop was served off the bone and felt more like pork belly. It was tender and felt like it had been cooked long and slow. The sauce was warming and tangy and fried egg on rice worked really well along side it.
If you've never had Vietnamese food please try this place, even if you have, try this place. This felt like really good home cooked food. If I lived here this would be a regular for us.

name: Cafe de Jaren
description:
een Amsterdams cafe met een internationaal team
Cafe de Jaren, geopend in 1990, is een licht en ruim cafe in het centrum van Amsterdam, gelegen tussen het Muntplein en het Muziektheater.

Binnen vormen hoge plafonds en veel ruimte een aantrekkelijke ambiance.

Aan de achterzijde bieden een balkon en een terras aan het water uitzicht op de Amstel.
Wie per boot arriveert, kan onze eigen aanlegsteiger gebruiken.

De Jaren dankt zijn populariteit aan de kwaliteit van het eten en drinken dat het serveert, de leestafel en de terrassen aan het water. En last but not least de gastvrijheid.

name: Palmyra Syrian Restaurant
description:
Van harte welkom in ons Palmyra Restaurant .
We willen u een greep uit onze culinaire Lebanese en Midden-Oosters keuken laten proeven met echt authentieke gerechten gemaakt door onze ervaren chef kok Ibrahim Hanna Shamoun .
Bij ons is het de traditie om onze gerechten met elkaar te delen zodat u alle smaken kunt proeven uit onze geweldige keuken van Speciale Grill en vegetarische gerechten
Welkom

name: Salsa Shop
description: Looking for a Mexican restaurant in Amsterdam? Salsa Shop Amsterdam at Rembrandt Square is your top choice. Enjoy the authentic Mexican food experience right here in the heart of Amsterdam. With a variety of delicious options available, whether you are craving for lunch, lekker eten, or simply want to explore restaurants near you, Salsa Shop has got you covered. It stands out among Amsterdam restaurants, offering a unique blend of traditional and modern Mexicaans food that you won't find elsewhere. Experience the best Mexicaans restaurant Amsterdam has to offer at Salsa Shop.

Each course presented an unexpected combination of flavors - some familiar, some I couldn't place even after the server had just explained to me everything that was in the dish. Immediately forgetting much of what I was eating may have worked in my favor, as I was able to detach from my expectations and just enjoy a completely invigorating sensory experience. Each course presented something as appealing to my eye as to my tongue, an exciting adventure all around.
There was plenty of time between each course, probably more than I would've liked. Altogether, my 5 course dinner took around 2 and a half hours. I only wish I'd brought a book to read between courses and people-watching.

The atmosphere was distinct. The design of the restaurant was industrial yet laid back. Rustic wood decorated the walls amidst tiles and concrete. A beautiful bright red ceiling balanced the slate gray of the floors. As a solo diner, I enjoyed taking it all in, watching the staff's impressive coordination and attentiveness as they moved through the dining area. My only qualm with the space itself was the bathrooms - clean enough, but between the small space and its position next to the coat rack, it felt a bit closet-like.

At 70 euros (not including wine pairings or other extras), the 5-course [vegetarian] menu was a more than worthwhile experience. Those dishes will stick with me, and they left me feeling inspired to seek out more adventures for my palate. We celebrated our wedding anniversary at Choux, with the five-course tasting menu, opting for everything vegetarian.

description:
Bij PLUK Reestraat 19 Amsterdam is het adres om samen met je vrienden en familie te genieten van geweldig lekkere coffee, heerlijke sandwiches, een gezond ontbijt of healthy lunch.
PLUK Reestraat 19 Amsterdam is the place to enjoy delicious coffee, sweets, sanwiches, breakfast and lund with your friends or family.

name: Thai Street Bar
description: Thai Street Bar is a very popular Isaan food cafe, providing a relaxed atmosphere whilst enjoying Thai food & drinks. There is also a special VIP booking service for special guests. We have a great selection of Thai drinks (alcohol & soft), as well as Heineken on tap. This is an authentic Thai Bar cafe & Thai meeting place. There is usually a little wait for the food but it is definitely worth it. We are the original authentic Thai Isaan cafe in Amsterdam,, with over 30 years selling at this location. Please remember this is a bar service primarily, so you will be expected to order a drink with your meal. Customers must vacate the premises before midnight.

name: Madre
description: Ontdek Madre, het leukste Mexicaanse restaurant in Amsterdam! Geniet van modern Mexicaanse gerechten bereid met verse ingredienten, zoveel lokaal en biologische gesourced. Of je nu zin hebt in een gezellige avond in het restaurant of in lekkere drankjes in de cocktailbar,Madre biedt de perfecte sfeer. Goed nieuws: we zijn nu ook op maandag geopend! Madre is de ideale plek voor iedereen die op zoek is naar Mexicaans eten in Amsterdam. Reserveer snel en ervaar het leukste restaurant in de stad!

The food is combines bold flavors with fresh, plant-based ingredients that elevate classic Mexican food to new heights. The dishes are thoughtfully prepared, with unique ingredients and seasonings that offer a delightful balance of textures and tastes. The live  guacamole was an interesting twist.

The drinks are equally impressive, with inventive cocktails and refreshing mocktails that perfectly complement the flavors of the food.

Whether you're a vegan or not, this restaurant offers a refreshing take on Mexican cuisine that is both satisfying and surprising. The atmosphere is vibrant and inviting, making it the perfect spot to enjoy a meal with friends or family.

You walk in through a narrow corridor, past a small bar and into the main area of the restaurant which has a modern 1920s vibe with satin lounges, as well as tables. To the right there is a huge open kitchen  where you can watch the kitchen staff prepare your meal. Service was very good! Attentive, friendly but not annoying. Empty plates were removed almost instantly and we could order quickly aswell. The food was DELICIOUS! All veggie and vegan and the concept allows to share. We had the mushroom tacos which were super tasty, the cauliflower wings (also great) and (the cherry on top) roasted Yacon with mole sauce. The Yacon really surprised me! The mix of the rather crisp and sweet tasting root mixed with the roasted aroma and the mole was perfect! Never had this before and I was definitely impressed!!
They also have their own Madre blond (in collaboration with Homeland Brewery) which tastes exotic and fresh and complements the dishes very well.
We spent 60EU in total and were saturated and satisfied. Definitely worth a visit!","published_at":"a month ago","published_at_date":"2024-11-28T13:40:01","response_from_owner_text":"Hello Alina!

We ordered "The Full Madre Experience," which included three starters, three main courses, and two desserts. The dishes were fantastic, though I have to say I didn't feel completely full afterward.

It would have been great if they had included the tortilla chips and freshly-made guacamole in the set, especially since they prepare it right at your table, which looked pretty impressive.

Overall, the price was fair, but I did leave a bit hungry. Still, the quality of the food made it worth trying.

The only downside was being charged 9EU for a Heineken, which was surprising.

Thank you again for sharing, it really helps us and we appreciate it a LOT!

Each of these is a very specific art form that ties restaurant has mastered. I sat next to a piano converted in bottles, giving a hint of what was to come. The waitstaff is attentive and unobtrusive, though more than willing to engage in conversation if you desire.

As one should, I chose the level 2 wines and six courses. Don't short yourself--you deserve to taste every thing this establishment had to offer.

Each course is delicately prepared. Every component is delicious in its own right and becomes part of a symphony when combined and paired with the wines. Han's explains the wines and courses in a matter of fact way, though with the underlying playfulness that you need for a good menu. He is personable and delightful.

The chef is an invisible force, creating her complex works of art in the kitchen. But you can see her dedication and desire to make good food in every plate. I'll confess, I poked my head in the kitchen to show my appreciation and she smiled in return.

The food and wine play together, highlighting different elements. A desert course brings out a licorice in the wine. A starter calms a wild briney Chardonnay.

Treat yourself to De Utrechtsefwarstafel. We opted for a nonalcoholic dinner, but friends who have visited highly recommend the wine pairing. Note that it's important to make a reservation in advance and even more important to confirm it when the owner reaches out via email, lest your reservation gets canceled. Which would be a real shame.

The pork cheek was absolutely delicious, the cod melts in your mouth like a warm hug, and the nectarine iced dessert was hands down the best dessert we've had in a long time. As for what can be improved, the first course of brined tuna was only good, not great. The various elements in the dish didn't love each other, the union more closely resembled an arranged marriage. However, the one thing I'd really change is the bread; no butter on Earth can improve the experience of crunching on a rock hard dinner roll. Those minor points aside, we had a delightful dinner and left more than satisfied.

name: Mata Hari
description:
Modern French-Mediterranean bistro menu with a creative twist. Join us for a candle-lit dinner in our cosy, art-deco style restaurant, or have a hand-crafted cocktail at the bar.

Step out of the rush and enter the hidden gem of Amsterdam's Red Light District. Feel at home, feast your eyes and lift your spirits. Let yourself be seduced by our passion for delicious food, exquisite drinks, solid hospitality, and a warm atmosphere.
At Mata Hari, the spirit of the Roaring Twenties gets re-awakened. Celebrate life and enjoy the moment!
